ere\nif prices had not already been not far\nabove the loan level.\nOn the basis of the Government fore\ncast traders foresaw the possibility of a\nsubstantial increase in carry-over stocks\nthis season and a large volume of cot\nton In the Government loan, perhaps well\nin excess of 3,000.000 bales. Larger sup\nplies were also expected to curb forward\nbuying of textiles. Prices in later deal\nings moved up 50 cents a bale from the\nextreme lows on mill buying and short\ncovefing.\nLate afternoon prices were 2.10 to 2.90\ni a bale lower than the previous close. Oc\ntober. 31.07; December, 31.23; March.\n31.32.\nOdd-Lot Dealings\nThe Securities and Exchange Commis\nsion reported today these transactions by\ncustomers with odd lot dealers or spe\ncialists on the New York 8tock Exchange\nfor August 6. 3.172 purchase involving\n89,937 shares. 2,889 sales involving\n80.416 shares including 17 short sales\ninvolving 805 ghares.\nSales\u2014\nStock ana Add Mel\nDividend Rate 00 Hlth. Low. 2:80. due\nWalgreen 1.60 1 33% 33% 33%\nWalker Hlrl Mis 1 23 23 23 .Ok\nWardBakink 2 15% 15% 15% Vi\n'Ward Bk nf5% 10 97% 97% 97%\nWarner Broi 1 7 10% 10% 10%\nWarren Pet 60 is 27% 27 27\nWayne Knit 1 40 2 18% 18% 18%-%\nWayne ruma 2 4 21% 21% 21%\nWesson 011 2'ah 34 34% 33% 33%\nWesson Oil n!4 110 82% 82% 82%+%\nWstlndSugl %a s 24 23% 23%\nW Penn Elec %e 7 18 17% 18\nIWs Penn El A 7 20 112% 112% 112%\ntWs Penn El nl7 20 117 11*% 116% -1\n'W PenFw 014% 10 108% 108% 108%\nW V\u00bb C&C 1.05* 4 20% 20% 20%\n1 45% 45% 45%\n2 7%\n2\n2\nWVa PuIdAP la\nWesternAir Line\nWeatAutoSup 1\nWestern Md\nWest lid 2nd nl.\nWest Pacific 3\n7% 7%\n38% 38% 38%\n13 13 13\n4 36% 36% 36%\n2 33% 33% 33%+\nWest On Tell*. 14 21% 21 21\nWest Air Brk 2. 4 37% 37% 37%-%\nWestlns Elec 1 13 28% 28% 28%\nWstngEInfBR 80 3 97\nWestvaco 1.40..\nt Wstvaco Pf3%\nWheel Steel 2 2 50% 50% 50%\n'Wheelstl prof5 40 88% 88% 88%\nWhite Mot 1 60 2 20% 20% 20%+%\nWhite SewlnsM 4 21\n\u2666White S M nf 4 270 56\n97 97\n2 43% 43% 43%\